clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Used in the treatment of prostate cancer Previously used in the prevention of miscarriage or premature delivery in pregnant women prone to miscarriage or premature delivery

contraindications.disease: Symptoms of overdose include nausea and vomiting and withdrawal bleeding may occur in females
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Diethylstilbestrol is a synthetic estrogen that was developed to supplement a woman s natural estrogen production In 1971 the Food and Drug Administration FDA issued a Drug Bulletin advising physicians to stop prescribing DES to pregnant women because it was linked to a rare vaginal cancer in female offspring
